Package: telepathy-kde
Architecture: all
Depends: telepathy-kde-contact-list,
 telepathy-kde-approver,
 telepathy-kde-text-ui,
 kde-config-telepathy-accounts,
 kde-config-telepathy-accounts-plugins,
 plasma-widget-telepathy-presence,
 telepathy-mission-control-5,
 telepathy-connection-manager,
 ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: telepathy-gabble
Suggests: telepathy-butterfly, telepathy-haze, telepathy-sunshine, telepathy-idle
Description: metapackage for installing all the Telepathy-KDE components
 Telepathy-KDE aims to integrate real-time communication and collaboration
 features into the KDE Plasma Workspaces. It provides means to connect
 to several instant messaging networks, chat with your friends and
 collaborate with them.
 .
 Telepathy-KDE consists of several independent components that need to be
 used together to provide all the available features. This package is
 a metapackage that installs all those components.
 .
 Apart from the dependencies that this metapackage pulls, you will also
 need to install at least one of the telepathy-gabble, telepathy-butterfly,
 telepathy-haze packages to be able to connect to your IM networks.
 gabble provides xmpp, butterfly provides msn and haze provides most other
 common protocols.
